{"/service/ndnp/ohi/batch_ohi_kaffirlily_ver01/data/sn85038220/00340580722/1949032801/0215.xml":{"full_text":"MARCH 28, 1948\nCollision at Square\nA 1941 Mercury owned by Rob\nert Dennis, of Marysville, was\nslightly. demaged Sunday after\nnoon when it was sideswiped by\na 1939 Packard driven uy Fred\nM. Cooperider, of Columbus. The\nThink of\n9\nSOT\n-_________________________________\u2014*\nIt went like this nt the Hooper\u2019s\nthe other night. Flap\u2019s eighteen\nyear-old daughter is talking about\n\u201ca real gone guy\u2014solid\u2014out of this\nWorld, but def.\"\n\u201cNow what kind of language is\nthat?\u201d Hap barks.\u201cCan\u2019t she speak\nEnglish?\u201d\n\u201cI\u2019ll translate it for you,\" Ma\nHooper says, \u201cin the language of\nthe twenties, when you were about\ntwenty years old. She simply means\nthis fellow is the \u2018cat\u2019s whiskers.*\nRemember how toe used to talk\nsometimes?\" Hap went back to\nreading his newspaper.\nLump.\naccident happened on the Public\nSquare. According to Constable\nGeorge Singer. Cooperider ap\nparently attempted to pass Den\nnis .and they scraped fenders. A\nfront fender of Dennis\u2019 car was\ndented while the Packard was\nundamaged.\nand OAUGHTE\nRI STPHOOF enamel snap fastener front I\nKuRDY-styied hooded Raincoat\nFREE plastic toaster cover with 2 Raincoats\n5*day money back guarantee if not delighted 4\nDAUGHTER'S COAT *1.59\nMOTHER'S COAT $1.93\ntrt?AVY \u00ab\u00abUJ\u00bb metallic Btutic In y#ur chv.v.\nbeautiful colort: Green, Blue, Silver, Wine. Styled with\na belt alt a/uund and attained hood, may be \u00bbxit\nor boxy over heavy lull, or -oati Order any 2 eoatt NOW\nand receive FREE a beautiful plattio toatter cover at our I\nlift ta yaw. SIZES Mother: SMall-MEOIUM\u2014LARQC\nOtuehter. 8\u201410\u201412\nPIMM (Mt\u00ab\nwrtf tt tian, lire, and -olon to to\nI\u00abnt K\u00ab9tfs\nKORDY SALES CO.\nFIFTH AVENVE.\nNFW FORK If.\nS. i 1 \u201di.-. K. i oi will I ii I i\nN. T.\nFrom where. I sitE. jy Joe. Marsfi\nRemember How\nWe Talked?\nBcpt.-W\njfrfrerrfteTW* z\nFrom where s!t, it\u2019s easy to\ncriticize the other person when we\ndon\u2019t take a good long look at our\nselves. Sure, there\u2019ll always be\nsome differences. I\u2019m fond of a\ntemperate glass of beer and maybe\nyou would prefer ginger ale\u2014but\nlet\u2019s just live and let live. Because\nwhen we go out of our way to find\nthings to find fault with in others,\nchances are they can find a few in\nus, too.\nCopyright, 1949, United States Brewers Foundation\nMiller's\nI UP FINE FURNITURE\n\"The Store For the Home\"\nMILLER FURNITURE STORE\nPhone 8071 Marysville, Ohio\nGuaranteed Watch Repairing\nRing a Date\non Your Calendar\nTo make you remember that\nyour watch needs cleaning and\nadjustment at least once a year\nto prevent wear! Periodic\ncleaning and adjustment at\nHildreth\u2019s will prolong its\nbenefits to you.\nPROMPT DELIVERY\nJust Call 2111\nA Good Coal For Every Furpose\nWm. J. CONRAD SON\nCOAL\nA Complete Supply of Ohio, West Virginia\nand Kentucky Coal. Tn Lump, Egg and Stoker\n\u00abizes. Aiso Berwind Briquets and Pocahontas\nCaryl Opposes I EPC Action\n(Continued from page 2)\ntice and to make such affirmative\naction including reinstatement or\nhiring of employees witn or with\nout back pay, as will effectuate\nthe purpose and policies of this\nact. This bill provides that the\ncommission shall have power to\npetition the court of common pleas\nof Franklin county, or the court\nof common pleas of the county\nwherein the unfair employment\npractice in question occurred or\nwherein any person charged with\nthe unfair employment resides or\ntransacts business, for the en\nforcement of such order and for\nappropriate relief or restraining\norder. The commission shall file\nwith iits petition a transcript of\nthe entire record in the proceed\ning, including the pleadings and\ntestimony upon which such order\nwas made and the findings and\n\u25a0order of the commission. Upon\nsuch filing, the court shall cause\nnotice thereof to be served upon\nsuch persons and shall issue such\ntemporary order as it deems just\nand proper, enforcing the order\nof the commission pending final\nhearing, and thereupon shall have\njurisdiction of the proceeding and\nof the question determined there\nin, and shall have power to grant\nsuch permanent relief or re\nstraining order as it deems just\nand proper, and to make and en\nter upon the pleadings, testimony\nand proceedings set forth in such\ntranscript a decree enforcing,\nas to modified, or setting aside in\nwhole or in part the order of the\n^commission. Violation\ncourt\u2019s decree shall be\nas a contempt thereof.\nGf the\npunished\nis in con-\nThe above paragraph\nflict with Article I, Section 16 of\nthe Ohio constitution which is as\nfollows: All courts shall be open,\nand. every person, for an injury\ndone him in his land, goods, per\nson, or reputation, shall have re\nmedy by due course of law, and\nshall have justice administered\nwithout denial or delay. In other\nwords, instead of this bill being\nconsistent with the constitution\nand particularly the above para\ngraph, it is in direct conflict with\nArticle I, Section 16 which says\nthat the court shall not have the\nright to enjoin the commission.\nWe are, therefore, denying the\nright of persons, the right to re\ndress to the courts and on the\ncontrary are permitting the com\nmission to dictate to the courts\nthat they shall enjoin the right\nof redress to the courts.\nThis bill provides that for the\npurpose of all investigations, pro\nceedings, or hearings which the\ncommission deems necessary or\nproper for the exercise of the\npowers vested in it by this act,\nth commission, or its authorized\nagents, shall at all reasonable\ntimes have the right to examine\nthe records and books of any per\nson being invesigated or pro\nceded against relating to any in\nvestigation, proceeding, or hear\ning, and that any member of the\n\u25a0commision or its authorized a\ngents shall have power to issue\nsubpoenas requiring the attend\nance and testimony of witnesses\nand the production of any evi\ndence relating to any investiga\ntion, proceeding, or hearing be\nfore the commision, its member\nor agent, conducting such in\nvestigation, proceeding, or hear\ning that agencies and officers of\nthe state or any political or civil\nsubdivision thereof shall furnish\nthe .commission, upon request,\nany record, paper, or informa\ntion in their possession relating to\nany matter before the commission\nand upon refusal to obey such\nsubponea or order said commis\nsion shall have jurisdiction to is\nsue to such person an order re\nquiring such person to appear be\nfore the commission, its member\nor agent, there to produce evi\ndence if so ordered, or there to\ngive testimony, touching the\nmatter under investigation or in\nquestion, and, any failure to o\nbey such order of the court may\nbe punished by said court as a\ncontempt thereof and the most\nvicious part of the bill, in line\n332, that no person shall be ex\ncused from attending and testi\nfying or from producing docu\nmetary or other evidence in obe\ndience to the subpoena of the\ncommission, on the ground that\nthe testimony or evidence re\nquired of him may tend to incrim\ninate him or subject him to a\npenalty or forfeiture. e\nThe provisions in this iTTWsure\nare extremely dangerous where\nin, if passed, they would be set\nting a precedent in giving an ap\npointive commission extraordin\nary powers it is exempt from the\nrules of evidence and rules of\nprocedure: it could hail before it\nany jemployer suspected of dis-\nORDER BABY CHICKS\nFrom the only Ohio\u2014U. S. Ap\nroved and U. S. Pulloram\nPassed hatchery in Union Co.\nGreater liveability is guaran\nteed as all flocks tosteU to\nzero reaction.\nPex 100 As hatched\nWe\nPullets\nAA\n$30\nAAA AA AAA\nWh. Leg. $16 $15\u2014$32\nWh. Bar. Rocks\nNew\nHamp. $16 $15\u2014$25\nAsk about Turkey Poult prices\nMcCullough's\n$24\nhatchery\nMarysville. O.\nPhone 4401 RED Ng. S\nTHE UNION COUNTY JOURNAL. MARYSVILLE. QHIO-\ncrimination and that employer\nwould not have normal protec\ntion of the law. In other words,\nthere are no qualifications as to\nthe training, the background for\nthe members who are to serve as\njudges of this commission. You\nmay not know it, but all the rules\nof evidence that we adhere to and\nthe rules of procedure that are\nfollowed in our courts of justice\nhave been enacted by this Legis\nlature. Now are we going to des\ntroy that judicial branch of our\ngovernment by delegating judi\ncial powers to a commission who,\naccording to this bill, could be\nmade up of anyone would not\nrequire the necessity of legal or\ntechnical training, but such ap\npointments as you might know\nwould be made by the governor\nin power at the time? This bill\nfurther provides that upon any\ninterference with the commission\nor violation of the provisions of\nthis act that such employer or\nother individual shall be guilty\nof a crime punishable by fine or\nimprisonment or both. The quali\nfications of this one-man court\nwould not be determined by the\nLegislature but by the F. E. P. C.\nin accordance with its rulemak\ning power. This commission or\nany of its agents would have the\npower to enter private business\nplaces and there conduct searches,\nexamine and copy any evidence\nof any person being investigated\nor proceeded against by such a\ngent, This bill makes no re\nquirement as to probable cause\nfor such search or the need for a\nsearch warrant. If the victim\nshould wilfully resist, impede, or\ninterefer with such a search he\nwould thereby become a criminal\nand subject to a fine of $1,000 and\none year imprisonment. Article\nI, Section 14 of the Ohio consti\ntution provides that the right of\nthe people to be secure in their\npersons, homes, papers, and po\nsessions against unreasonable\nsearches and seizures shall not be\nviolated and no warrant shall be\nissued upon probable cause sup\nported by Gath or affirmation,\nparticularly describing the place\nto be search and the posessions\nand things to be seized. They say\nin this bill that you have a\nright to appeal to the courts. It\nalso provides that the findings\nof the Board shall be conclusive.\nTherefore, the reviewing court\nwould only review the record or\ntranscript of the proceedings that\nwere held by this commission un\nder no rules of evidence or pro\ncedure other than their own, as\nprovided they have a right to\nmake, which would mean- that\nthe court would not have the\npower to pass on the credibility of\nthe witnesses who testified in the\nhearing before the commission\nit could not pass on the truth or\nfalsity of the testimony it. would\nnot pass upon the issues of whe\nther it is a trumped-up law\nby a blackmailer or shyster,\ncourt would not have the\nnesses before it in order\nsuch would have the opportunity\nto study the demeanor of the\nsuit\nThe\nwit\nthat\nwitnesses while upon the wit\nness stand and observe him as to\nhis candor or fairness, his inter\nest in the outcome of the litiga\ntion or the lack thereof.\nThis is setting a very danger\nous procedure in that the com\nmission is empowered to sub\npoena suspects and witnesses and\nto use the courts to enforce this\npower, but the person subpoenaed\ndoes not have the right before\nthe commission that he would\nhave in the courts that the com\npelled to underwrite the com\nmission\u2019s authority. The penal\nties provided in this bill are se\nverely drawn and dangerous to\nliberty. Under this bill one who\nhelps to make a record of a pros\npective employee\u2019s religious affili\nation in his employee\u2019s files is\nsubject to a fine of $1,000 or a\nyear's imprisonment or both.\nYou membei-s, if you don\u2019t\nknow that our constitution pro\nvides that any person charged\nwith a capital or infamous crime\nshall be indicted by a grand\njury in the county where the al\nleged crime is supposed to have\ntaken place that he shall be\nserved with a copy of such indict\nment describing the offense\ncharged against him that he is\nentitled to a speedy public trial\nbefore a jury of his peers: that\nhe is entitled to be represented\nby counsel, is entitled to com\npulsory process, may subpoena\nwitnesses all over the world to\ntestify on his behalf at the ex\npense of his government: shall\nnot be required to testify against\nhimself is presumed to be inno\ncent until proven guilty by the\nstate or the government and that\nregree of guilt must be beyond a\nreasonable doubt and that all\nmembers of the jury before\nwhom he is tried must concur in\nthe finding of a verdict .against\nhim. If this legislation were en\nacted, as you will note, it applies\nto the state and the various po\nlitical subdivisions which would\npermit this commission or any of\nits agents to go into the sheriff\u2019s\noffice in any county, into the\nauditor\u2019s office where the per\nsonal property tax returns are se\ncret and such officials would be\nsubject to a fine and imprison\nment for any interference with\nthe commission or any of its a\ngents according to this bill could\nbe many because there is no limit\nplaced upon the number of agents.\nNow are you going to say that\nwhen one is accused of crime\nthat this Legislature is going to\ntear down all the safeguards of\nour constitution and permit a\ncommission of fanatics and un\nquilificd people to dictate to our\njudiciary which is made up of the\nbest talent of the land and are\nmen who have spent years in\ntraining and preparation to cope\nwith and meet the occasions as\nthey arise and for the past hun\ndred years or more there has been\nbut very little complaint or disa\ngreement with our judiciary.\nloDuyT\nOi Not to Buy\nrend this short article in\n.Garrison\u2019s, a magazine for inde\npendent retailers, written by Mr.\nL. !Roy Bigge and we thought it\nso timely and to the point that\nwe asked and received the per\nmission of the publisher to re\npublish it. We feel whether you\u2019re\nfarmer, on employee, or a fel\nlow man in business this story\nhas a message for you.\n\u2018There was a man who lived by the side of the road and sold hot dogs.\nHe was hard of hearing so he had no radio.\nHe had trouble with his eyes so he read no newspapers.\nBut he sold good hot dogs.\nHe put up signs on the highway telling how good they were.\nHe stood on the side of the road and cried: \u201cBuy a hot dog Mister?\u201d\nAnd people bought.\nHe increased his meat and bun orders.\nHe bought a bigger stove to take care of his trade.\nHe finally got his son home frop college to help him out.\nBut then something happened.\u2019\nHis son said, \u201cFather haven\u2019t you been listening to the radio?\nHa vent\u2019 you been reading the newspapers?\nThere\u2019s a big recession on,\nThe European situation is terrible.\nThe domestic situation is worse.\u201d\nWhereupon the father thought, \u201cWell, my son\u2019s been to college,\nhe reads the papers and he listens to the radio,\nand he ought to know.\u201d\nSo the father cut down on his meat and bun orders,\ntook down his advertising signs,\nand no longer bothered to stand out on the highway to sell hot dogs.\nAnd his hot dog sales fell almost overnight.\n\u201cYour\u2019e right sori, the father said to the boy.\n\u201cWe certainly are in the middle of a great recession\u201d.\u2019\nWeiss Brothers\nPLASTIC\nTable\nWhite and Colored\nLace and other pretty\npatterns\nGood Quality\nsidered. When this legislation by\nlaw delegates the authority that\nman or commission can force\nAmerican citizens to employ or\nbe associated with, against their\nwill, any person, that day Demo\ncracy dies.\nIf we want to eause race riots,\ndestruction of property, and the\nabandoment of the system of\nprivate ownership, pass this bill.\nI predict here and now that if\nthis bill ever becomes law an a\nroused American public opinion\nwill drive from public office\nevery person who votes for this\npassage*.\nThe F. E. P. C. would take con\ntrol of hiring, an arm of the\ngovernment would be telling em\nployers whom they could hire,\npromote, and discharge. An em\nployer would not be safe in hir\ning. firing, upgrading unless he\nasked some unqualified agent a\nbout his business. Many employ\ners would give up the ship. Many\nemployers have set up small\nplants to give jobs to their sons,\nfamilies, neighbors, or members\nof their church. That is his right\nWe will never be able to legis\nlate against a mental attitude.\nTh is country was founded upon\nfaith that people would do the\nright thing. The habits and atti-,\ntudes of the people must be con-\u2019 in a Democracy. During the time\nThrifty Wednesday\nMorning Special\nntotniWm:tiririffirrrj^.ainaiuidntf^cmmranacTuuinnmr^iuiiauuiguimuiugiuaiiiinuiinnnauntqinu:.:i.:\nActual $1.49 Values\n52x52 Heavy 3-ply\n'nn'Tirff- mnrnj n i frmi ujpinup jayoelbninxniuininBaunifiraifruxi\nGet the \"Wednesday Morning\" Habit\nOpen Till 10 p.m. Beginning This Sat\nWEISS BROTHERS\nof widespread unemployment, the\nproblem of F. E. P. C. would be\nmost dangerous. Many of those\ndropped from the pay rolls would\nbring up discrimination and you\nwould see more litigation and\nshakedowns and more shyster\nlawyers trying to got rich than\nyou have ever seen before. It is\napparent to all but those who re\nfuse to see that the F. E. P. C. is\nnothing but a major objective of\nthe Communist party. It is de\nsigned to destroy our Republi\ncan form of government, regi\nment the nation\u2019s business and in\ndustry. Enactment of this legis\nlation alone would do more to\ncreat social and industrial dis\nunity than any other piece of\nlegislation ever considered.\nSection 13 of this bill defines\n\u25a0page Three.\npersons as follows: The term\n\u201cperson\u201d includes one or more\nindividuals, partnerships, asso\nciations, organizations, corpora\ntions, legal representatives, trus\ntees, trustees in bankruptcy, or\nreceivers, and the state and all po\nlitical subdivisions, boards and\ncommissions thereof. Some of\nyou constitutional lawyers should\nknow if you have ever practiced\nin the United States District\nCourt that a trustee in bank\nruptcy is an officer of the United\nStates District Court and if this\nF. E. P. C. legislation becomes\nlaw it would permit the commis\nsion or its agents to interfere witl\na trustee in bankruptcy, and as\nresult, you would in all proba\nbility have the commission and al\nof its agents in jail where the^\nbelong\nyou're tho cantor of attraction\nwith flawless, flattering Nylon* by\nHOLEPROOF. Proportioned in width\nas well as in length for perfect,\nwrinkle-free fit. And w\u00bb have a\ncomplete range of sheer* to fit\nevery wearing\nOpen Till 10 p. m. Beginning This Sat.\nneed ift your\nenticing \"foicinafion\nColors.\u201d\nwitchfry\ntfGUIlL\nCoQUflTE\n(NC HA NT\nWeiss Bros\nIrldMMftt brow*\ndramatic t\u00a9up\nAun-warm Ui\u00abe\nrich copper","height":"27111","width":"21762"}}
